        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(opencode-go): re-arm idle timer on block-boundary events to prevent false stalled-stream abort",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nWhen the opencode-go model finalizes a tool call and deliberates before the\nnext one, the provider emits real block-boundary SSE events\n(`text_end`, `thinking_end`, `toolcall_start`, `toolcall_end`) that prove the\nsocket is alive. The stalled-stream watchdog only treated token deltas as\nprogress, so the idle timer could fire, abort a live stream, replace a\ncompleted answer with a stalled error, and drop the provider's real `done`\nevent.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\n`isProviderProgressEvent` now treats all four block-boundary events as\nprogress. `text_start` and `thinking_start` remain excluded because they are\nsynthetic preamble events and must not shorten the first-event window.\n\n## User Impact\n\nLive opencode-go answers are no longer falsely classified as stalled while\nthe provider is emitting valid block-boundary events between deltas.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/opencode-go/stream-termination.test.ts`\n  — 12 passed, including the boundary-event regression.\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/llm-idle-timeout.test.ts`\n  — 92 passed.\n- `git diff --check` — clean.\n- The regression drives the real stream wrapper with boundary events spaced\n  below `idleTimeoutMs` and asserts that no false abort occurs.\n\nCloses #96518\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-96518-boundary-liveness",
